Hi Jason,

Can I please ask you to review my message below and confirm if you can do something about the pending credit card transactions on the website?

Thanks,

Jason

Hi All,

I have read everything and tried the new donation method on the website now to get a better understanding of how things play out.

So it looks like this method (with the change to stripe payments) tracks whether or not someone completes the payment form on stripe or not. If they don't they go to an "Incomplete Transaction" on stripe. We will probably need to ignore these transactions as for the most part it is just simply form abandonment.

One thing I do note is that the transactions on the WordPress side now goes to "Pending" as well. This is regardless of whether the transaction successfully completes or not on the Stripe side. This does not work well for the gift processing team as they will now need to go through each transaction and mark them as published in order for us to extract those donations out of the website. Is this something that we have to keep like this, or can the website check with stripe as to whether the payment was successful or not? Heath, if you can confirm this, that would be great.

I have checked the 2 Funraisin sites that we have and can verify that neither use the MS Research Australia account for stripe transactions those transactions do not exist on either Funraisin site. What I was also able to determine is that they have a webhook callback to msra.org.au. so maybe they did exist on the site originally? All that I know is that the transaction code seems to represent a "Payment Intent" which typically means that the person did not follow through on completing their transaction. Some of the reasons included not providing payment details, or not receiving a confirmation, perhaps from the donation form? Maybe it is a result of a timeout.

After you have made the change Heath, it looks like those "Payment Intents" don't seem to have occurred anymore, we just are ending up with a lot more incomplete payments as we are tracking all of the donation form abandonments that we haven't done before. But I would like to see if we can automate the pending for successful transactions from pending to published so my processing team does not have manage this. If not, I think we need to explore a different solution to this problem, as having to do this for PayPal transactions previously (now fixed AFAIK) was quite tedious and problematic.

Thanks,

Jason

Kind regards

Hi Neil, 

It appears that payment was actually deemed a security risk by Stripe's policies. I can explain more about this if you like. Generally this is the result of something suspicious. For example a common one is a credit card that has been issued in country 'A' that is being charged in country 'B'. 

If you can send me a link to the fundraisin donation page I can see if that's the one.

Thanks Heath,

For investigating these rogue donations and for the Loom presentation explaining your changes.

Concerned that from the example that there is a $2K missed donation from Denis Hume and that from just the example screen you are showing.

It looks as though my colleagues who have been using Funraisin platform should be able to assist us hopefully with this matter of concern.

Thanks again,

Neil
